 — Argentine President Javier Milei signed a decree authorizing the entry of U.S. troops into the South American country for joint military exercises

 The decision allows American personnel and equipment from their Armed Forces to participate in the operation called Atlantic Dagger, scheduled to take place between April 21 and June 12, as well as in the naval operation PASSEX, which will occur from April 26 to 30.

  The joint exercises will be carried out at different military installations across the country, including the Puerto Belgrano Naval Base, the Córdoba Military Garrison, and the VII Air Brigade of the Argentine Air Force, located in Moreno, in the province of Buenos Aires.

 In turn, the second operation will take place in Argentina’s Exclusive Economic Zone and will include the participation of U.S. Navy vessels, operating alongside local units.

 The initiative represents a new step by the United States to expand its influence in Latin America. President Javier Milei has become one of Donald Trump’s main allies in the region.

